    LORE_RELIC_WARDEN_SILENT_WHISTLE = [[
This whistle looks like carved bone polished by years of handling. No one remembers who first carried it, only that it turned up in records after the first time a patrol came back from the deepwood with fewer injuries than expected and more stories about odd quiet.

When blown, the Silent Whistle does not make a sound that most hunters can hear. Instead, it pulls the forest a breath back, dampening branches and small-creature scurries just enough for trained ears to pick out the wrong footstep or the misplaced twig-snap.

Used too often, it earns the forest’s annoyance, and birds will leave entire routes empty for days. Used when it matters, it can mean the difference between an ambush and a stand. The whistle has never worked for anyone who wanted it for parade ground drills.]],


    LORE_RELIC_THORNSHADE_MANTLE = [[
